Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Finely chop @pecans{1/2%oz} (or crush in their bag with a #heavy pan{} or #rolling pin{}).

Adjust rack to top position if using salmon.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Let cool slightly, then stir in chopped pecans, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Honey Mustard Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @honey{2%tsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, and @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}.

== Salmon ==

Pat @skin-on salmon{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with remaining @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Evenly spread tops of salmon with a thin layer of honey mustard sauce (save the rest for serving). Mound with pecan mixture, pressing firmly to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast on middle rack until crust is golden brown and salmon is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.

== Lemony Apple Salad ==

Meanwhile, halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%oz} and apple with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and as much lemon juice as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide salmon and salad between plates. Drizzle salmon with remaining honey mustard sauce. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Swap in chicken instead of salmon; roast on top rack, 15-20 minutes.

> Weeknight luxury is just 30 minutes away!